Carve-outs (these are NOT covered by this proprietary license; their
upstream licenses control):

1. Files under `vendor/**` are third-party Go modules vendored via
   `go mod vendor`. Each subdirectory contains its own LICENSE
   (MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, or ISC). Those
   licenses continue to apply to those files.

2. Files under `.claude/skills/**` are third-party Claude Code skills
   from Anthropic, the community, and other authors. Each subdirectory
   contains its own LICENSE / LICENSE.source / LICENSE.txt. Those
   licenses continue to apply to those files.

3. `LICENSE-third-party.md` documents attribution requirements for
   bundled fonts (SIL Open Font License 1.1) and the optional
   IP2Location LITE GeoIP database (Creative Commons Attribution-
   ShareAlike 4.0). Those upstream licenses control those assets.

4. The compiled Go binary `statnive-live` linked from this source
   incorporates the vendored dependencies in (1) under their MIT /
   Apache / BSD / ISC terms. Compliance manifests are produced by
   `go-licenses` at release time and shipped in
   `releases/<version>/licenses.json`.

Everything else in this repository — including but not limited to the
